04:39.046 --> 04:41.782
♪♪ WE DO THE BEST THAT WE CAN ♪♪

04:41.815 --> 04:44.785
♪♪ WE DO THE BEST THAT WE CAN ♪♪

04:44.818 --> 04:46.153
NO. BAD IDEA.

04:46.186 --> 04:48.722
THIS FAMILY
NEEDS SOME FUN.

04:48.755 --> 04:50.490
WAY TOO MANY PEOPLE.

04:50.524 --> 04:52.726
COME ON. WHO'S GONNA SPOT US
IN THE MIDDLE OF MONTANA?

04:52.759 --> 04:55.395
OKAY.
YOU JUST PUT ME IN CHARGE.

04:55.429 --> 04:57.698
MOMENTUM. SECLUSION.
ANDY'S PLAN.

04:57.731 --> 04:59.132
Silas: HE'S RIGHT.

04:59.166 --> 05:01.502
THIS DOESN'T SEEM LIKE
THE SMARTEST IDEA RIGHT NOW.

05:01.535 --> 05:03.737
I CAN'T BELIEVE I HAVE TO
CONVINCE YOU GUYS

05:03.770 --> 05:04.905
TO GO TO A GIANT CARNIVAL!

05:04.938 --> 05:07.774
LOOK, THERE'S A RODEO!

05:07.808 --> 05:10.444
AND A ROLLER COASTER.

05:14.915 --> 05:16.717
REALLY?

05:16.750 --> 05:17.651
YEAH.

05:21.989 --> 05:24.057
WAIT.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

05:24.091 --> 05:26.426
THAT WAS JUDAH'S THING ‐‐
ROLLER COASTERS.

05:26.460 --> 05:27.628
REALLY?

05:27.661 --> 05:29.963
OH, I THOUGHT HE WAS KIDDING
WHEN HE SAID HE DESIGNED THOSE.

05:29.997 --> 05:31.732
WHAT DID YOU THINK
HE DID FOR A LIVING?

05:31.765 --> 05:33.267
NEVER REALLY CARED.

05:33.300 --> 05:37.004
REMEMBER THAT ONE IDEA HE HAD
WHERE THE SEATS FLIPPED

05:37.037 --> 05:38.472
SO YOU DIDN'T ACTUALLY
GO UPSIDE DOWN?

05:38.505 --> 05:41.375
OH, AND DAVID BOWIE MUSIC
WAS PUMPED INTO THE HEADREST!

05:41.408 --> 05:42.910
"LIGHTNING FRIGHTENING."
[ CHUCKLES ] RIGHT.

05:42.943 --> 05:45.212
KEPT A MODEL OF IT
IN THE GARAGE.

05:45.245 --> 05:47.314
YEAH, AND HE ALWAYS TOOK US
TO THAT ONE AT SIX FLAGS,

05:47.347 --> 05:48.615
LIKE,
EVERY OTHER WEEKEND.

05:48.649 --> 05:50.384
THAT SETTLES IT.
WE'RE GOING.

05:50.417 --> 05:52.719
NANCE, I ‐‐
FOR OLD TIME'S SAKE.

05:52.753 --> 05:53.787
PLUS,
SHANE HAS BEEN KIDNAPPED.

05:53.820 --> 05:57.057
IT'S VERY TRAUMATIC,
BEING KIDNAPPED.

05:57.090 --> 05:58.892
MM. I WOULDN'T KNOW.

05:58.926 --> 06:00.827
TWO HOURS, TOPS.

06:00.861 --> 06:03.163
I WANT EVERYBODY TO CLEAN UP
BEFORE WE GET BACK INTO THE CAR.

06:03.197 --> 06:05.666
CHANGE YOUR ‐‐ YOUR SHIRTS
AND YOUR UNDERWEAR.

06:05.699 --> 06:07.734
HYGIENE ‐‐ STILL IMPORTANT.

06:10.037 --> 06:12.339
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:12.372 --> 06:14.875
YOU NEED TO KEEP YOUR HAT ON
AT ALL TIMES.

06:14.908 --> 06:17.077
THESE PLACES HAVE
TIGHT SECURITY ‐‐

06:17.110 --> 06:18.679
CAMERAS,
UNDERCOVER POLICE.

06:18.712 --> 06:21.682
THAT BEARDED LADY OVER THERE ‐‐
NOT A LADY AT ALL.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.784
SAFETY ‐‐ WE GOT IT.
RELAX.

06:23.817 --> 06:25.419
RELAX?
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:25.452 --> 06:27.020
'CAUSE YOU'RE A ‐‐
YOU'RE A SQUEAKY FIELD MOUSE

06:27.054 --> 06:28.889
HEADED INTO A BEAR CAVE,

06:28.922 --> 06:32.025
EXCEPT THE CAVE
IS A SWARM OF PEOPLE, OKAY?

06:32.059 --> 06:33.360
AND THE MOUSE
IS YOUR OWN EGO.

06:33.393 --> 06:36.230
WAIT, THE CAVE IS ‐‐
THE C‐‐ YOU GET MY POINT.

06:36.263 --> 06:37.431
EGO. YES.
EGO, EGO.

06:37.464 --> 06:40.033
WILLFUL DEFIANCE,
'CAUSE I LAID DOWN RULES,

06:40.067 --> 06:41.468
BUT YOU HAD TO
BREAK THEM.

06:41.502 --> 06:43.437
I AM HERE BECAUSE
I DON'T WANT MY KID

06:43.470 --> 06:46.073
TO MISS OUT ON HIS ENTIRE
FUCKING CHILDHOOD, OKAY?

06:46.106 --> 06:47.407
IT'S JUST FUN!

06:47.441 --> 06:49.643
SEE THE WAY I HELD THAT GUN
ON IGNACIO?

06:49.676 --> 06:52.479
CAVED LIKE A COAL MINE.
FUCKING PAYASO AMATEUR.

06:52.513 --> 06:55.616
SHANE, GET OVER YOURSELF.
NO ONE CARES.

06:55.649 --> 06:57.317
YOU'RE JUST JEALOUS.
OF WHAT?

06:57.351 --> 06:59.620
THAT MOM
LIKES ME BETTER NOW.

06:59.653 --> 07:02.256
Man: PINWHEELS
AND WHIRLIGIGS!

07:02.289 --> 07:04.725
GET YOUR PINWHEELS
AND WHIRLIGIGS!

07:04.758 --> 07:06.593
5 FOR $10!

07:06.627 --> 07:07.995
IT SPINS! IT WHIRLS!

07:08.028 --> 07:11.031
IT'S A HEE‐HAW,
FIRE‐CRACKING WHIRLIGIG!

07:11.064 --> 07:13.033
[ Laughing ] WOW.
DO YOU WANT ONE?

07:13.066 --> 07:14.568
SOUNDS LAME.

07:14.601 --> 07:16.703
NOPE. THANKS, THOUGH.

07:16.737 --> 07:18.539
HAVE A GOOD DAY.

07:18.572 --> 07:19.540
Man on P. A.: <i>FIRST PRIZE</i>

07:19.573 --> 07:21.975
IN THE 21st ANNUAL
BUTTER SCULPTURE CONTEST ‐‐

07:22.009 --> 07:23.510
<i>A LUXURY MOTOR HOME.</i>

07:23.544 --> 07:25.379
WINNER TODAY CAN DRIVE HER HOME
<i>TOMORROW.</i>

07:25.412 --> 07:27.181
<i>THAT'S RIGHT, FOLKS.</i>
<i>A LUXURY MOTOR HOME.</i>

07:27.214 --> 07:28.815
THE WINNER TODAY CAN DRIVE
<i>HER HOME TOMORROW.</i>

07:28.849 --> 07:32.553
REMIND ME AGAIN WHERE WE'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE SLEEPING TONIGHT.

07:32.586 --> 07:35.222
DOUG, WATCH THE BABY.

07:37.457 --> 07:38.725
Doug: YEAH, DON'T WORRY
ABOUT ME. ASSHOLES.

07:38.759 --> 07:40.394
[ COOING ]

07:46.500 --> 07:48.168
WOW!
[ GASPS ]

07:48.202 --> 07:49.903
THIS THING'S INSANE.

07:49.937 --> 07:51.371
WE COULD LIVE HERE.

07:51.405 --> 07:53.674
WE SHOULD. SHOULD.
WE SHOULD LIVE HERE.

07:53.707 --> 07:54.975
KITCHEN, LIVING ROOM,
BEDROOM.

07:55.008 --> 07:56.877
WE COULD SET UP
A LITTLE NURSERY.

07:56.910 --> 07:58.612
OH! IS THIS CORIAN?

07:58.645 --> 08:00.881
WE WOULDN'T HAVE TO STAY
IN CRAPPY MOTELS.

08:00.914 --> 08:03.383
WE COULD STAY AT...
NATIONAL PARKS

08:03.417 --> 08:06.687
UP IN THE, LIKE, MOUNTAINS,
ANYWHERE.

08:06.720 --> 08:08.388
PLUS, WE NEED TO DUMP
CESAR'S CAR.

08:08.422 --> 08:11.425
YES. BLACK TOWN CAR ‐‐
CLASSIC BAD‐GUY MOBILE.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.760
VERY CONSPICUOUS.

08:13.794 --> 08:15.295
ANDY...

08:15.329 --> 08:16.496
WIN THIS.

08:16.530 --> 08:17.998
ON IT.
AH!

08:18.031 --> 08:21.068
SO, WHAT,
IT'S LIKE A CONTEST?

08:21.101 --> 08:22.469
"BUTTER...SCULPTING"?

08:22.503 --> 08:25.539
YEAH, I HAVE NO IDEA,
BUT I'M A CONSUMMATE CONTESTANT.

08:25.572 --> 08:29.576
I WIN SHIT ALL THE TIME.
TRUST ME, IT'S IN THE BAG.

08:29.610 --> 08:30.944
DOUG.

08:30.978 --> 08:33.347
DOUG, I'M GONNA PRETEND

08:33.380 --> 08:35.482
THAT YOU AREN'T THE REASON
THAT WE WERE TRACKED DOWN

08:35.516 --> 08:37.618
AND ASK YOU TO WATCH STEVIE
FOR THE AFTERNOON.

08:37.651 --> 08:39.152
NANCE,
I RAISED FOUR KIDS.

08:39.186 --> 08:40.954
TRUST ME,
THEY ALL TURNED OUT ‐‐

08:40.988 --> 08:43.457
WELL,
I RAISED FOUR KIDS.

08:43.490 --> 08:47.761
OKAY, SO THERE'S A FULL BOTTLE
OF FORMULA IN THE STROLLER.

08:47.794 --> 08:49.363
HE LIKES BIRD ‐‐
BIRD SOUNDS.

08:49.396 --> 08:51.865
UM, NO SOLID FOOD,
OBVIOUSLY.
OKAY.

08:51.899 --> 08:53.767
NO SHARP, POINTY OBJECTS.

08:53.800 --> 08:55.269
I'M GOOD WITH BABIES.

08:55.302 --> 08:58.639
THEY SEE ME AS A KINDRED SPIRIT/
TALLER VERSION OF THEMSELVES.

08:58.672 --> 08:59.540
GO. BE FREE.

08:59.573 --> 09:01.975
I'M TED WILSON NOW ‐‐
VERY RESPONSIBLE.

09:07.748 --> 09:11.051
I COULD BE A CARNY.

09:11.084 --> 09:13.820
DRIVING FROM CITY TO CITY,
HANDING OUT PRIZES.

09:13.854 --> 09:15.389
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:15.422 --> 09:18.358
I ONCE DRESSED UP LIKE
THE MUFFIN MAN FOR HALLOWEEN.

09:18.392 --> 09:20.093
TRUE STORY.

09:22.429 --> 09:26.166
HANDED OUT MUFFINS
TO ALL THE NEIGHBORHOOD KIDS.

09:26.200 --> 09:28.001
[ Laughing ]
I DON'T EVEN LIKE MUFFINS.

09:28.035 --> 09:29.436
[ SNIFFLES ]

09:29.469 --> 09:31.705
HOW DO YOU SAY "MUFFIN"
IN MEXICAN?

09:31.738 --> 09:34.708
OH, RIGHT.
YOU CAN'T TALK STILL.

09:34.741 --> 09:37.277
HOW ABOUT THIS, CHEECH?

09:37.311 --> 09:39.046
HOW ABOUT WE DITCH
THIS DEN OF CREEPY SADNESS

09:39.079 --> 09:40.547
AND GO HAVE
SOME REAL FUN?

09:40.581 --> 09:41.548
HOW ABOUT THAT?

09:41.582 --> 09:43.984
YEAH. ME TOO.

09:46.220 --> 09:47.487
HA!

09:48.822 --> 09:51.758
WAS IT COOL ‐‐
SHOOTING SOMEONE?

09:51.792 --> 09:54.728
NO, IT WASN'T COOL.
IT WASN'T COOL.

09:54.761 --> 09:56.063
HOW MANY TIMES
DO I HAVE TO TELL YOU?

09:56.096 --> 09:57.731
VIOLENCE ISN'T COOL.

09:57.764 --> 10:00.434
ARE YOU MAD AT ME?

10:00.467 --> 10:01.802
NO, I'M NOT MAD.

10:01.835 --> 10:04.037
YOU S‐‐
YOU SOUND MAD.
I'M NOT MAD.

10:04.071 --> 10:06.673
I'M...WORRIED
THAT YOU'RE BECOMING ‐‐

10:06.707 --> 10:09.643
LIKE <i>YOU?</i>

10:09.676 --> 10:11.645
W‐WHAT? NO.
THAT'S NOT ‐‐

10:11.678 --> 10:12.713
WE'RE THE SAME.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.448
OKAY.

10:14.481 --> 10:16.483
DON'T TRY TO TELL ME
WHAT I AM, ALL RIGHT?

10:16.517 --> 10:17.684
I KNOW WHAT I AM.

10:17.718 --> 10:19.520
I'VE BEEN WHAT I AM
A LOT LONGER

10:19.553 --> 10:21.955
THAN YOU'VE BEEN
WHAT YOU...MAYBE ARE.

10:21.989 --> 10:24.958
AND...

10:24.992 --> 10:28.662
EVEN IF YOU ARE,
"LIKE ME,"

10:28.695 --> 10:30.464
YOU'RE STILL A BOY ‐‐

10:30.497 --> 10:32.132
SMART, S‐SO SMART,

10:32.165 --> 10:34.635
BUT A LITTLE LOST.

10:34.668 --> 10:37.204
AND, SHANE, LISTEN.

10:37.237 --> 10:40.240
IT'S MY JOB TO MAKE SURE

10:40.274 --> 10:43.110
YOU DON'T TURN OUT
TO BE A PSYCHOPATH, OKAY?

10:43.143 --> 10:45.913
SO, IF THAT MEANS DRAGGING YOU
TO SOME AMUSEMENT PARK

10:45.946 --> 10:47.781
OR ‐‐ OR SLAPPING YOU
ON THE HEAD

10:47.814 --> 10:49.750
EVERY TIME YOU SAY
"CUNT" OR "BITCH"

10:49.783 --> 10:51.685
OR "MOTHERFUCKING CUNT,"

10:51.718 --> 10:54.288
I'M GONNA FUCKING DO IT,
OKAY?

10:54.321 --> 10:56.056
BECAUSE
I'M STILL YOUR MOM,

10:56.089 --> 11:00.394
AND I HAVEN'T FINISHED...
TRYING TO BE YOUR MOM.

11:00.427 --> 11:02.496
OKAY?

11:02.529 --> 11:03.664
UNDERSTOOD?

11:03.697 --> 11:05.699
YEAH.

11:13.507 --> 11:14.675
HI.

11:14.708 --> 11:17.644
I WOULD LIKE TO SIGN UP FOR YOUR
BUTTER‐SCULPTURE CONTEST.

11:17.678 --> 11:19.780
ME TOO.
UH, BIG SCULPTING FAN.

11:19.813 --> 11:21.348
GOT SOME
POTTERY EXPERIENCE.

11:21.381 --> 11:24.151
NEVER WORKED
IN THE BUTTER MEDIUM BEFORE,

11:24.184 --> 11:26.253
ALTHOUGH I ONCE MADE
AN AZTEC TEMPLE

11:26.286 --> 11:28.522
OUT OF GUMMY WORMS
AND MARSHMALLOWS.

11:29.656 --> 11:32.759
I LIKE ART, IN GENERAL.

11:32.793 --> 11:34.194
WELL,
WE'D LOVE TO HAVE YOU.

11:34.228 --> 11:36.663
ALWAYS NICE TO HAVE
A FATHER/SON TEAM AT THE TABLE.

11:36.697 --> 11:39.766
I JUST NEED YOU TO SCRIBBLE DOWN
YOUR JOHN HANCOCKS RIGHT HERE.

11:41.635 --> 11:44.371
ONLY FOUR PEOPLE?
HUH.

11:44.404 --> 11:46.440
POOL GETS SMALLER
EVERY YEAR.

11:46.473 --> 11:48.876
REALLY? 'CAUSE I FIGURED,
UH, YOU KNOW,

11:48.909 --> 11:50.878
IT'S SUCH
A LUSTROUS PRIZE ‐‐

11:50.911 --> 11:52.446
SHE'S A BEAUT, ISN'T SHE?

11:52.479 --> 11:55.883
APOLLO LEGEND, LUXURY CLASS‐A,
360 HORSEPOWER,

11:55.916 --> 11:57.484
EVEN HAS
A FOLD‐OUT VERANDA.

11:57.518 --> 11:59.253
OKAY. WOW.

11:59.286 --> 12:00.921
DONATION
FROM OUR CORPORATE SPONSOR ‐‐

12:00.954 --> 12:02.356
BIGBUTTER FAMILY,

12:02.389 --> 12:04.224
OWNS MOST
OF SOUTHERN MONTANA.

12:04.258 --> 12:08.328
WHAT EXACTLY IS
A BUTTER SCULPTURE?

12:11.798 --> 12:13.367
OH.

12:13.400 --> 12:15.702
MONTANA'S
SONS AND DAUGHTERS

12:15.736 --> 12:16.603
CARVED IN BUTTER.

12:16.637 --> 12:18.071
SO TH‐‐ THEY'RE PRE‐MADE?

12:18.105 --> 12:19.306
30 POUNDS EACH.

12:19.339 --> 12:21.475
HAD TO KEEP THEM
IN A ROTATING COOLER ALL NIGHT.

12:21.508 --> 12:24.845
IT'S A SHAME
THEY GOT TO BE DESTROYED.

12:24.878 --> 12:26.813
DESTROYED BECAUSE...

12:26.847 --> 12:28.749
IT'S AN EATING CONTEST.

12:29.816 --> 12:31.585
WE MAKE 'EM,
YOU EAT 'EM.

12:33.053 --> 12:34.488
RIGHT.
EW.

12:34.521 --> 12:37.758
ANYWHO, CONTEST STARTS
IN 20 MINUTES...

12:37.791 --> 12:40.427
RANDY AND MICHAEL.

12:47.034 --> 12:50.671
Shane:
THIS LINE IS RIDICULOUS.

12:50.704 --> 12:52.606
CAN'T WE JUST CUT?

12:52.639 --> 12:53.907
WHAT DID WE
JUST TALK ABOUT?

12:53.941 --> 12:55.542
CURSING. VIOLENCE.

12:55.576 --> 12:57.811
RESPECT.
SELF‐CONTROL.

12:57.845 --> 13:00.547
I JUST THINK OUTLAWS
DON'T WAIT IN LINE.

13:00.581 --> 13:02.749
OUTLAWS ALSO DON'T REFER
TO THEMSELVES AS "OUTLAWS,"

13:02.783 --> 13:05.752
JUST FYI.

13:05.786 --> 13:07.588
SO, WHAT NOW?

13:07.621 --> 13:09.223
WE WAIT.

13:09.957 --> 13:11.658
Woman: HONEY.

13:11.692 --> 13:14.228
...HOW MUCH FUCKING
GOVERNMENT‐SUBSIDIZED CORN
WE CAN GROW ON THAT LAND?

13:14.261 --> 13:16.930
IN FACT, WE DON'T HAVE TO
GROW IT, AND THEY'LL PAY US.

13:16.964 --> 13:18.832
MOM, MOM, MOM, MOM!
ONE MORE, ONE MORE.

13:18.866 --> 13:19.867
MOM!

13:19.900 --> 13:21.568
YEAH.

13:21.602 --> 13:22.870
YOU HAVING
A GOOD TIME?

13:22.903 --> 13:23.804
YEAH.

13:23.837 --> 13:25.405
THIS IS TAKING
FUCKING FOREVER.

13:25.439 --> 13:28.275
WE SHOULD DO
MORE THINGS TOGETHER.

13:28.308 --> 13:29.376
WE SHOULD.

13:29.409 --> 13:30.777
YOUR DAD
WOULD'VE LIKED THAT.

13:30.811 --> 13:32.112
LOOK AT THESE PEOPLE.

13:32.145 --> 13:34.681
DO YOU MISS HIM?

13:34.715 --> 13:36.483
YEAH. I DO, YEAH.

13:36.517 --> 13:39.686
BUT...WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO, RIGHT?
FUCK THIS.
COME ON.

13:42.656 --> 13:43.690
GET IN HERE
AND STAY QUIET.

13:43.724 --> 13:44.925
FOLLOW DADDY.

13:44.958 --> 13:47.060
UH, MOM...

13:49.229 --> 13:52.065
YEAH, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
WE'LL ALL GET ON EVENTUALLY.

13:52.099 --> 13:54.134
THEY TOTALLY JUST CUT.

13:54.168 --> 13:55.369
I KNOW,
BUT THEY'RE IDIOTS.

13:55.402 --> 13:57.070
THE PEOPLE IN LINE
ARE GONNA GET PISSED.

13:57.104 --> 13:58.972
THEY'RE GONNA END UP
IN THE BACK, WHERE THEY BELONG.

13:59.006 --> 14:01.108
48...49...

14:01.141 --> 14:02.743
SORRY, FOLKS.
RIDE'S CLOSING.

14:02.776 --> 14:05.212
WE OPEN TOMORROW AT 10:00
IF YOU WANT TO COME BACK.

14:05.245 --> 14:06.613
YOU'VE GOT TO BE
KIDDING ME.

14:06.647 --> 14:08.715
MIDWAY CLOSES EARLY
ON WEDNESDAYS FOR MAINTENANCE.

14:08.749 --> 14:11.118
WELL, LOOK, UM,

14:11.151 --> 14:15.789
MY ‐‐ MY LATE HUSBAND ‐‐
THIS YOUNG BOY'S DEAD FATHER ‐‐

14:15.822 --> 14:17.457
UM, WAS A ROLLER‐COASTER
DESIGNER,

14:17.491 --> 14:19.626
SO IT'S KIND OF
A FAMILY TRADITION.

14:19.660 --> 14:21.128
WHAT'S TWO MORE PEOPLE?

14:21.161 --> 14:24.798
IF I LET YOU ON,
I'D HAVE TO LET EVERYBODY.

14:24.831 --> 14:27.634
RIGHT.

14:27.668 --> 14:29.670
OKAY. WAIT HERE.

14:29.703 --> 14:31.238
I'M COMING.

14:33.941 --> 14:36.143
EXCUSE ME.
WHAT?

14:36.176 --> 14:38.645
I BELIEVE THAT YOU WERE
BEHIND ME IN THE LINE.

14:38.679 --> 14:40.314
NO.

14:40.347 --> 14:42.683
UM, YES.

14:45.719 --> 14:48.222
YOU GUYS AREN'T GONNA
SAY ANYTHING?

14:48.255 --> 14:50.924
THIS MAN JUST CUT
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOU.

14:50.958 --> 14:52.059
IT'S OKAY.

14:52.092 --> 14:54.094
LOOK, LADY.
WE'RE NOT BREAKING ANY LAWS.

14:54.127 --> 14:58.532
SO? IT'S COMPLETELY
UNACCEPTABLE AND...RUDE!

14:58.565 --> 15:00.767
NOT TO MENTION CRAPPY!

15:00.801 --> 15:02.503
EXCUSE ME.
WHAT ABOUT YOU?

15:02.536 --> 15:05.172
BIG MAN?
YOU WERE BEHIND ME IN LINE.

15:05.205 --> 15:07.007
THIS GUY CUT
IN FRONT OF US.

15:07.040 --> 15:08.842
COME HERE, COME HERE.
YOU GONNA LET HIM DO THAT?

15:08.876 --> 15:12.246
YOU'RE GONNA LET HIM
DO WHATEVER HE WANTS
AND WALK ALL OVER YOU?

15:12.279 --> 15:14.414
FUCK NO.

15:14.448 --> 15:15.482
FUCK NO!

15:15.516 --> 15:18.619
HEY, BRUCE, GET THE FUCK
OUT OF LINE, YOU CUTTER.

15:18.652 --> 15:20.454
LICK MY BALLS, JIMMY.

15:20.487 --> 15:22.189
YOU'RE JUST MAD
'CAUSE I THOUGHT OF IT FIRST.

15:22.222 --> 15:24.892
HEY,
THAT AIN'T RIGHT!
SHUT IT, SANDY!

15:24.925 --> 15:26.493
HEY, YOU DON'T SAY, "SHUT IT,"
TO MY WIFE.

15:26.527 --> 15:28.662
SHE WAS MY WIFE FIRST!
BEEN THERE, DONE THAT.

15:28.695 --> 15:29.796
I TRADED UP, NED!

15:29.830 --> 15:30.797
FUCK YOU!

15:30.831 --> 15:32.032
KICK HIS ASS!
HEY!

15:32.065 --> 15:33.433
GET IN THERE, HONEY!
KICK HIS ASS!

15:33.467 --> 15:34.868
KICK HIS ASS!

15:34.902 --> 15:37.271
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

15:47.748 --> 15:50.450
OKAY.

15:50.484 --> 15:52.419
HERE YOU GO.

15:52.452 --> 15:53.587
JUST LET THE FLAVOR
MELT IN YOUR MOUTH.

15:53.620 --> 15:57.191
WASH IT DOWN
WITH A LITTLE BIT OF ICE CREAM.

16:02.996 --> 16:04.998
HUNGRY YET?

16:05.032 --> 16:08.569
NOT ENOUGH TO EAT 30 POUNDS
OF MILK FAT. YOU?

16:08.602 --> 16:10.671
GETTING THERE.

16:10.704 --> 16:12.806
THIS IS TASTY.

16:12.840 --> 16:14.575
IT'S LEFT OVER
FROM SEATTLE.

16:14.608 --> 16:18.111
JUST ADDED A LITTLE CINNAMON
FOR FLAVOR.

16:18.145 --> 16:20.380
SOMETIMES I THINK
YOU'RE THE SON I NEVER HAD.

16:20.414 --> 16:22.616
THANKS.

16:22.649 --> 16:25.586
I'M SERIOUS.

16:25.619 --> 16:27.721
I FEEL A SPECIAL KINSHIP.

16:27.754 --> 16:31.458
BECAUSE...WE'RE RELATED.

16:31.491 --> 16:34.695
I'M TALKING
SPIRITUAL KINSHIP.

16:34.728 --> 16:36.730
A SHARED SENSITIVITY
OF THE SPIRIT

16:36.763 --> 16:40.200
COMBINED WITH WHAT I LIKE
TO CALL UNTAPPED POTENTIAL.

16:40.234 --> 16:43.070
PLUS, THE WHOLE "SNEAKING
ONTO A COLLEGE CAMPUS" THING ‐‐

16:43.103 --> 16:45.739
VERY ANDY CIRCA '87.

16:45.772 --> 16:47.374
I'M APPLYING.

16:47.407 --> 16:49.610
[ SCOFFS ] WHAT?

16:49.643 --> 16:51.211
OR MIKE NEWMAN IS.

16:51.245 --> 16:54.548
I GRABBED A COMMON APP
BACK IN SEATTLE.

16:54.581 --> 16:56.183
Does Mom know?

16:56.216 --> 16:58.619
NO.
AND YOU CAN'T TELL HER.

16:58.652 --> 16:59.720
PROMISE?

16:59.753 --> 17:01.622
YEAH, I ‐‐ OKAY.

17:01.655 --> 17:02.789
WOW.

17:02.823 --> 17:05.225
REALLY? OKAY.

17:05.259 --> 17:08.195
THERE'S THIS QUESTION
ON THE APPLICATION.

17:08.228 --> 17:10.531
"EVALUATE
A SIGNIFICANT EXPERIENCE,

17:10.564 --> 17:13.834
ACHIEVEMENT, OR ETHICAL DILEMMA
YOU'VE FACED."

17:13.867 --> 17:17.337
[ Laughing ]
ETHICAL DILEMMA.

17:17.371 --> 17:20.974
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA ‐‐
[ Laughing ] I DON'T KNOW.

17:22.643 --> 17:24.444
BUT...

17:24.478 --> 17:27.714
I DO KNOW I DON'T WANT TO END UP
LIKE MOM AND SHANE.

17:27.748 --> 17:28.949
HEY! COME ON.

17:28.982 --> 17:32.319
THEY'RE FLAWED...

17:32.352 --> 17:34.855
LIKE US,
LIKE EVERYBODY.

17:34.888 --> 17:36.323
I'M SERIOUS.

17:36.356 --> 17:40.460
I FEEL LIKE A COMPLETE ASSHOLE
FOR STEALING KIMMI'S CAR.

17:40.494 --> 17:45.666
I WANT TO EARN MY OWN WAY
OR WHATEVER...

17:45.699 --> 17:49.603
DO THINGS...

17:49.636 --> 17:51.605
DO THINGS RIGHT.

17:52.706 --> 17:55.976
<i>RANDY AND MIKE NEWMAN</i>
<i>TO THE DAIRY PLATFORM.</i>

17:56.009 --> 17:57.377
<i>RANDY AND MIKE NEWMAN</i>

17:57.411 --> 18:00.647
<i>PLEASE REPORT</i>
<i>TO THE DAIRY PLATFORM.</i>

18:00.681 --> 18:03.016
OH! THAT'S US.

18:11.191 --> 18:13.760
♪♪ THE KENTUCKY PILL ♪♪

18:13.794 --> 18:16.697
♪♪ AND A COW‐TIPPING EXPEDITION ♪♪

18:16.730 --> 18:18.432
♪♪ AND I'VE SEEN A FULLER MOON ♪♪

18:18.465 --> 18:21.568
♪♪ SWINGING WANTON PREMONITION ♪♪

18:21.602 --> 18:22.803
[ AIR HORN BLOWS ]

18:22.836 --> 18:24.671
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

18:24.705 --> 18:27.040
♪♪ ...THAN THIS OR THAT? ♪♪

18:30.878 --> 18:32.946
♪♪ 'CAUSE THERE'S BELIEVING ♪♪

18:32.980 --> 18:37.084
♪♪ AND THERE'S
TAKING OFF YOUR HAT ♪♪

18:37.117 --> 18:39.920
[ CHEERING CONTINUES ]

18:39.953 --> 18:42.556
♪♪ AND THERE'S READING ♪♪

18:42.589 --> 18:47.027
♪♪ AND THERE'S READING
THIS OR THAT ♪♪

18:50.430 --> 18:56.737
♪♪ I'M RUNNING
FOR MY OLD PLAYMATES ♪♪

18:56.770 --> 19:00.040
[ MACHINE‐GUN FIRE ]

19:00.073 --> 19:02.042
HUH?
[ LAUGHS ]

19:02.075 --> 19:04.878
♪♪ I'M RUNNING WITH A GUN ♪♪

19:04.912 --> 19:07.147
♪♪ THAT'S GONNA SHOOT... ♪♪

19:07.181 --> 19:10.284
YOU'RE NEXT, BUDDY.
GET READY.

19:14.922 --> 19:16.590
DON'T SMILE.

19:16.623 --> 19:18.659
YOU HAVE TO TRY THINGS
THE RIGHT WAY FIRST.

19:18.692 --> 19:20.594
THEN, AND ONLY THEN,

19:20.627 --> 19:23.130
INCITE A CROWD,
WHATEVER.

19:23.163 --> 19:25.098
DON'T TELL UNCLE ANDY
WE CUT THE LINE.

19:25.132 --> 19:30.704
♪♪ I LIED TO YOU WHEN YOU WORE
THOSE OTHER CLOTHES ♪♪

19:34.408 --> 19:37.511
♪♪ I WAS INTO YOUR THINKING ♪♪

19:37.544 --> 19:40.447
♪♪ "WHERE CAN I GET
ONE OF THOSE?" ♪♪

19:44.117 --> 19:46.553
♪♪ I WOULD'VE
PICKED YOUR BRAINS ♪♪

19:46.587 --> 19:50.991
♪♪ I WOULD'VE PAID YOU
THROUGH THE NOSE ♪♪

19:51.024 --> 19:53.660
[ RIDERS SCREAMING ]

19:53.694 --> 19:56.296
♪♪ AND THE GIRLS THAT YOU SEE ♪♪

19:56.330 --> 19:59.766
♪♪ THEY'RE ALL FASTER
THAN A TRAIN ♪♪

19:59.800 --> 20:01.101
Doug: WHOO!

20:01.134 --> 20:03.270
[ SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY ]

20:03.303 --> 20:04.471
OH!

20:04.505 --> 20:11.144
♪♪ LEFT THE CHANGES DOWN
TO FATE AND HAPPENSTANCE ♪♪

20:13.247 --> 20:15.482
♪♪ PICKED A VIEWPOINT ♪♪

20:15.516 --> 20:18.652
[ STOMACH GURGLING ]
♪♪ OH, AND HOW MY GIRL ♪♪

20:18.685 --> 20:21.455
♪♪ CAN DANCE ♪♪

20:21.488 --> 20:23.590
WE HAVE A WINNER!

20:23.624 --> 20:25.559
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

20:25.592 --> 20:28.962
♪♪ REALIZED SHE WAS
WATERING THE PLANTS ♪♪

20:28.996 --> 20:31.765
[ VOMITING ]

20:31.798 --> 20:33.667
[ RIDERS SCREAMING ]

20:33.700 --> 20:35.569
[ LAUGHS ]
HOO!

20:35.602 --> 20:38.972
[ BELL RINGS ]

20:42.676 --> 20:45.812
IS, UH ‐‐
IS HE GONNA BE OKAY?

20:45.846 --> 20:47.381
HE'S FINE ‐‐
MINOR HEART ATTACK.

20:47.414 --> 20:49.816
NOT GOOD FOR THE TICKER,
EATING THAT MUCH BUTTER.

20:49.850 --> 20:51.151
RIGHT.

20:51.185 --> 20:52.819
THAT WAS SOME WORK
YOU DID BACK THERE!

20:52.853 --> 20:56.723
I KNOW!
I WAS A PROUD FATHER TODAY.

20:56.757 --> 20:59.660
THANKS.
I FEEL PRETTY GROSS.

20:59.693 --> 21:03.297
I'M SURE THAT'LL PASS
WHEN YOU'RE SITTING IN
YOUR BRAND‐NEW MOBILE HOME.

21:03.330 --> 21:05.065
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

21:05.098 --> 21:06.700
SO, HOW DO WE DO THIS?

21:06.733 --> 21:08.502
IS THERE A CLAIM CENTER
OR...

21:08.535 --> 21:10.204
OH, NO, NO, NO.
RIGHT ‐‐ RIGHT HERE.

21:10.237 --> 21:12.840
GOT, UH, SOME FORMS TO FILL OUT,
TAX MUMBO JUMBO.

21:12.873 --> 21:15.442
FORMS?

21:15.475 --> 21:17.477
YEAH, STATE LAW REQUIRES
US TO SUBMIT SOCIAL
SECURITY NUMBERS

21:17.511 --> 21:20.480
TO THE COUNTY CLERK BEFORE WE
HAND OUT ANY MAJOR PRIZES.

21:20.514 --> 21:25.519
ONLY EXCEPTIONS ARE ANTIQUES
AND TROPICAL FISH.

21:25.552 --> 21:28.989
AND WHAT IF WE ‐‐

21:29.022 --> 21:31.325
HE DOESN'T HAVE
A SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER?

21:31.358 --> 21:34.528
THAT'S FINE. JUST JOT DOWN
YOUR TAX I. D. NUMBER.

21:38.799 --> 21:40.501
UM,
CAN WE HAVE A MINUTE?
SURE.

21:40.534 --> 21:42.503
OH, WHEN YOU'RE DONE,
THEY'RE GONNA WANT TO TAKE

21:42.536 --> 21:45.606
A PICTURE OF THE BIG WINNER
FOR THE <i>CHRONICLE.</i>

21:48.742 --> 21:50.477
Fucking damn it.

21:50.511 --> 21:53.313
HOW WAS HE?
GREAT.
NAPPED MOST OF THE DAY.

21:53.347 --> 21:55.649
AND YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT THOSE BIRD SOUNDS.

21:55.682 --> 21:57.684
SLEEP, CHIRP,
SLEEP, CHIRP.

21:57.718 --> 21:59.720
DOUG?
WHAT?
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

21:59.753 --> 22:00.687
IT'S STILL FULL.

22:00.721 --> 22:02.055
HE WASN'T HUNGRY.

22:02.089 --> 22:04.791
IRRESPONSIBLE, DOUG.
HE'S A BABY.

22:04.825 --> 22:06.493
HE NEEDS HIS BOTTLE.

22:06.527 --> 22:10.364
JESUS CHRIST, IT'S LIKE I
HAVE TO DO EVERYTHING MYSELF.

22:12.099 --> 22:14.601
THANKS...FOR TODAY.

22:14.635 --> 22:17.070
I LOVE YOU.

22:18.071 --> 22:20.107
BUT GET IN THE BACK.

22:20.140 --> 22:21.708
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

22:41.662 --> 22:42.829
ARE YOU MAD AT ME?

22:42.863 --> 22:44.298
YES, I'M MAD AT YOU!

22:44.331 --> 22:46.300
I WAS GIVING YOU
THE SILENT TREATMENT.

22:46.333 --> 22:48.202
OH, COME ON.
YOU HAD FUN.

22:48.235 --> 22:50.904
I HAD ‐‐
OKAY, I HAD A LITTLE FUN.

22:50.938 --> 22:52.673
BUT YOU STOLE MY POWER,

22:52.706 --> 22:55.742
UNDERCUT MY AUTHORITY WITHIN
SECONDS OF GIVING ME THE REINS.

22:55.776 --> 22:57.377
NOW YOU'RE
BACK IN CHARGE.
YEAH.

22:57.411 --> 22:58.812
WHY DON'T I BELIEVE THAT?
OH, RIGHT.

22:58.846 --> 23:01.515
'CAUSE THE LAST TIME YOU SAID
IT, YOU TOOK A SIX‐HOUR DETOUR.

23:01.548 --> 23:05.285
TODAY WAS SOMETHING
I NEEDED TO DO.

23:05.319 --> 23:07.754
PLEASE?

23:07.788 --> 23:10.324
ANDY?

23:15.696 --> 23:16.964
[ SNIFFLES ]

23:16.997 --> 23:18.999
KEEP HEADING EAST ON 80.

23:19.032 --> 23:21.602
I'LL SEE IF I CAN FIND US
A NEW ROUTE.

23:23.470 --> 23:25.873
[ SCOFFS ] HEY.

23:25.906 --> 23:27.574
CHECK IT OUT.

23:32.746 --> 23:37.017
♪♪ I'M TAKING A LONG WALK ♪♪

23:37.050 --> 23:41.855
♪♪ OFF OF A SHORT PIER ♪♪

23:41.889 --> 23:44.892
♪♪ ONE STEP TOO MANY ♪♪

23:44.925 --> 23:50.731
♪♪ AND DOWN I GO ♪♪

23:50.764 --> 23:55.903
♪♪ I'M TAKING A LONG WALK ♪♪

23:55.936 --> 24:00.574
♪♪ OFF OF A SHORT PIER ♪♪

24:00.607 --> 24:03.977
♪♪ FOR MY APPOINTMENT ♪♪

24:04.011 --> 24:08.215
♪♪ WITH COUSTEAU ♪♪

